snippet.textDisplay:
Bungo: "We want this to be an awesome action MMO."

Also Bungo: Releases expansions with so little content it shouldn't be called an expansion with 3 hour long campaigns, one new activity, two strikes, and only one full set of armor for each class along with only one new raid.

You see my point? If they want this to be an MMO, they're going to need the content of one, which means expansions the size of one like The Burning Crusade from WoW, the content updates of games like GW2, and the stories of ESO. Is it really that hard to make content that you gotta make the interesting stuff locked behind a couple paywalls? At the very least have the amount of content an MMO usually has when Destiny 3 or another expansion releases.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm kinda burnt out on D2.
Buuuuuut, I have a great idea for D3.
So, I was thinking, get rid of the annual pass and all DLC's.if bungie consistently will give us brand new FREE content, I'll be willing to pay 40 quid. Another thing. The campaign is too repetetive. Go somewhere, scan something, protect ghost while he's scanning, shoot something, big explosion, done. Make the missions more varied. Give us that goddam mission where we get to control our spaceship, and blow stuff up that way. Make some missions a... Defence mission? You know, like don't let any enemy get somewhere, just generally make the missions more varied.
I also want like a secondary campaign where you might not always be the same character, but it's all about uncovering the history of the guardians and more, so we can finally understand the lore. Make guns more varied too. Like, every single 150 rpm revolver kills in 3 headshots and has the exact same recoil. CHANGE it up a bit, yknow.
Mismatched armour looks disgusting, so bring back the shaders system from D1. And instead of having armours different sets, make another slot where we put in a style, so our armour always looks the same, except exotics. LESSEN THE GRIND. WE DON'T WANT TO PRAY TO RNG ALL THE TIME.
Thank you for listening.



And if you want to be even more cash money, let the hunters Wall run as well as double jump. Even if we lose the dodge.

If bungie does this, then it's very cash money of them

snippet.textDisplay: I'm a new player to Destiny 2 primarily, but honestly... I really wish there was more coverage on when a game picks itself up. I remember when Destiny 2 was getting covered day and night by YouTubers who hated on the game and proclaimed it was pretty much dead. Now that Destiny 2 is doing so well for itself and it's doing amazing, those same YouTubers who made clickbait rage videos aren't willing to make videos admiring the developers and the hard work that was put into improving the game for its players. Off topic I know, but just a little rant I wanted to get off my chest.
